<div class=3D"accordionItemWrapper"> <a href=3D"https://m.measurementconver=
sions.org/speeds/" class=3D"accordionButton currentAccordion"><span class=
=3D"abiR accordionButtonIcon"></span><span class=3D"accordionButtonTitle">I=
mperial Units</span></a>
<div class=3D"accordionContentWrapper" style=3D"display:block;">
<div class=3D"accordionContent">
<p>For those countries that use imperial distances the most common unit of =
speed is miles per hour (mph, miph, m/h, mi/h).=20
Occasionally inches per second (in/s, ips), feet per second (ft/s, fps), ya=
rds per second (yd/s, yps) and=20
miles per second (mi/s, m/s, mps) are also seen. It is extremely rare to se=
e the -1 superscript=20
notation used for imperial speed unit abbreviations.</p>
<h3>Table of Imperial Speed Units</h3>
<table>
<tbody><tr>
<td>Unit</td>
<td class=3D"tdcent">Abbreviation</td>
<td>As m s<span class=3D"sup">-1</span></td>
<td>Useful Information</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>inches per second</td>
<td class=3D"tdcent">in/s</td>
<td>0.0254</td>
<td>Rarely used</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>feet per second</td>
<td class=3D"tdcent">ft/s</td>
<td>0.3048</td>
<td>Rarely used</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>yards per second</td>
<td class=3D"tdcent">yd/s</td>
<td>0.9144</td>
<td>Rarely used</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>miles per second</td>
<td class=3D"tdcent">mi/s</td>
<td>1609.344</td>
<td>Rarely used</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>miles per hour</td>
<td class=3D"tdcent">mph</td>
<td>0.44704</td>
<td>Commonly used for road speed limits. Other abbreviations include mi/h, =
miph, m/h</td>
</tr>     =20
</tbody></table>
</div>
</div>
